<div id="pf5f" class="pf w5 h10" data-page-no="5f"><div class="pc pc5f w5 h10"><div class="t m5dc x78 hb y1b5 ff2 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">church went for direction (Acts 1:20); there the great preachers of Acts </div><div class="t m11c x28 hb y658 ff2 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">pointed those to whom they witnessed (Acts 3:19-26). </div><div class="t m5dd x28 hc yba7 ff1 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">VI. WITNESSING TO THE WORLD. </div><div class="t m505 x41 hc yba8 ff1 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. </div><div class="t m30c x6 hc y920 ff1 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Equipped for Witness (Luke 10:1, 2, 16; Acts 11:23, 24). </div><div class="t m2cd x1d hc yba9 ff1 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How has God prepared the way for success to attend our witnessing </div><div class="t m4fd x28 hc ybaa ff1 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">endeavors? Luke 10:18, 19; Rev. 12:9-11. </div><div class="t m424 x41 hb yaf9 ff2 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">While the devil still brings woe to the world (Rev. 12:12), God restricts </div><div class="t m465 x28 hb yafa ff2 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">his activity in time and authority (Rev. 13:12). Therefore &quot;even the devils </div><div class="t m551 x28 hb yafb ff2 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">are subject unto us through thy name&quot; (Luke 10:17); therefore evil men </div><div class="t m4c5 x28 hb y90 ff2 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">must stand back from God&apos;s cause (Acts 13:10, 11); therefore those who </div><div class="t m5de x28 hb y2dc ff2 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">persecute face judgment (Acts 12:23). </div><div class="t m4b6 x41 hc y531 ff1 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Where does our final authority to witness reside? Acts 2:32, 33; Luke </div><div class="t m2b3 x28 hc y532 ff1 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">22:29. </div><div class="t m5df x41 hb ye9 ff2 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;There is nothing that the Saviour desires so much as agents who will </div><div class="t m14e x28 hb ybab ff2 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">represent to the world His Spirit and His character. There is nothing that the </div><div class="t m5e0 x28 hb ybac ff2 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">world needs so much as the manifestation through humanity of the Saviour&apos;s </div><div class="t m5e1 x3 hb ybad ff2 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">love. All heaven is waiting for men and women through whom God can </div><div class="t m5e2 x3 hb yae5 ff2 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">reveal the power of Christianity. </div><div class="t m5c6 x6b hb y8f6 ff3 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;â€”The Acts of the Apostles, </div><div class="t m52f x47 hb y8f6 ff2 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">p. 600. </div><div class="t m1b9 x5c hc ybae ff1 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m4ad x5d hc ybaf ff1 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Using Every Opportunity (Luke 13:1-5; Acts 26:28, 29). </div><div class="t m5e3 x5c hb ybb0 ff2 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">In Jesus&apos; discussion about faith (Luke 17:5-18:8) He tells us to work </div><div class="t m462 x3 hb ybb1 ff2 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">without expecting praise for our efforts. Doing so gives evidence of faith </div><div class="t m3dd x3 hb ybb2 ff2 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(17:10). He points to the grateful Samaritan who gave glory to God for what </div><div class="t m44f x3 hb ybb3 ff2 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Jesus had done. Doing so also gives evidence of faith (17:18, 19). </div><div class="t m5e4 x5c hc y647 ff1 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What should be our constant concern in a world of uncertainty and </div><div class="t m5e5 x3 hc yb49 ff1 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">risk? Luke 13:1-5. </div><div class="t m2ab x3 hc y404 ff1 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">VII. ONWARD TO THE WORLD. </div><div class="t m5e6 x5c hc y64e ff1 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">In what spirit should we approach the limitations that health or cir-</div><div class="t m5b8 x3 hc ybb4 ff1 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">cumstance may place on our ability to witness? Acts 28:20; Luke 23:33, </div><div class="t m5e7 x3 hc y259 ff1 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">43. </div><div class="t m5e8 xb2 hb y13a ff2 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">95 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
